---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="AI Training – Onyx Labs"
  description="Role-based AI training for product, engineering, and leadership teams."
>
  <section class="content-main">
    <div class="container shell">
      <div class="content-layout">
        <div>
          <div class="content-kicker">AI Training</div>
          <h1 class="content-heading">Give every team a practical AI toolbox.</h1>
          <p class="content-lede">
            We design and deliver role-based AI training so your product, engineering, data, and
            leadership teams can use AI safely and effectively in their day-to-day work.
          </p>
          <div class="content-tags">
            <span class="tag">Product Enablement</span>
            <span class="tag">Engineering Deep Dives</span>
            <span class="tag">Executive Briefings</span>
            <span class="tag">Hands-on Workshops</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <aside class="content-panel">
          <h3>Formats we offer</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>1–2 hour executive briefings.</li>
            <li>Half-day practitioner workshops.</li>
            <li>Multi-week cohort-based learning.</li>
            <li>Custom internal playbooks and guides.</li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </div>

      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="content-panel">
          <h3>For product & design</h3>
          <p>
            Help product managers and designers understand what AI can (and can't) do today, how
            to frame good problems, and how to partner with legal and engineering.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Discovering high-leverage AI use-cases in your product.</li>
            <li>Prompt and UX patterns that actually ship.</li>
            <li>Partnering with governance and risk without losing speed.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="content-panel">
          <h3>For engineering & data</h3>
          <p>
            Deep dives on architectures, evaluation, and safety for teams building or integrating
            AI systems.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Patterns for integrating foundation models and APIs.</li>
            <li>Evaluation, monitoring, and red-teaming techniques.</li>
            <li>Data privacy, retention, and access considerations.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-section">
        <div class="section-header flex justify-between align-items-start flex-wrap gap-3 mb-3">
          <div>
            <div class="section-title">Sample programs</div>
            <p class="section-subtitle mb-0">
              We tailor each program to your industry, stack, and governance model.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-grid">
          <div class="card-onyx">
            <div class="card-label">Leadership</div>
            <div class="card-title">Executive AI strategy briefing</div>
            <p class="card-body-text">
              A concise session covering the AI landscape, risks, and how to prioritize investment
              in your context.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-onyx">
            <div class="card-label">Product</div>
            <div class="card-title">Designing AI-native features</div>
            <p class="card-body-text">
              Hands-on workshop where teams ideate, scope, and de-risk concrete AI features for
              your roadmap.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-onyx">
            <div class="card-label">Engineering</div>
            <div class="card-title">LLM evaluation in production</div>
            <p class="card-body-text">
              Practitioners learn how to evaluate model quality, safety, and drift with real
              tooling and examples.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
